sentences: Herman Autrey (December 4, 1904 – June 14, 1980) was an American jazz trumpeter.
After some time in Florida he worked in Washington, D.C., Philadelphia, and New York City, where he played with Charlie Johnson in 1933.
He became well known through Fats Waller, who hired him in 1934 after signing a contract with Victor Records.
Autrey worked as a sideman into the 1940s with Stuff Smith, Sammy Price, and Una Mae Carlisle.
Early in the 1950s Autrey was hurt in a car crash, sidelining his career for one year.
